In <ct.760348003@login.dkuug.dk> ct@login.dkuug.dk (Claus T|ndering) writes:

>Some governments forbid ordinary citizens to use encryption. And
>sometimes the mere fact that an encrypted message is sent will
>arouse suspicion. There must therefore be a need for a method
>to make an encrypted text look as if it were a normal innocent
>text.

>So:
>Are there any automated methods for disguising an encrypted text
>as plaintext?

There is a Macintosh app called Stego that encodes a file into the
lsb's of a Mac PICT file. Look on ghost.dsi.unimi.it:pub/crypt.

Hiding in plaintext is a little trickier, but it has been done by
hand for centuries so I am sure the inquiring mind can think of a
way to do it automatically.


